*vpopmail-5.2.1-r4 (10 Feb 2003)

  10 Feb 2003; Nick Hadaway <raker@gentoo.org> vpopmail-5.2.1-r4.ebuild,
  files/digest-vpopmail-5.2.1-r4 :
  changed mysql logic so if mysql is not in use to force disabling of
  mysql support.

*vpopmail-5.2.1-r3 (05 Feb 2003)

  05 Feb 2003; Nick Hadaway <raker@gentoo.org> vpopmail-5.2.1-r3.ebuild,
  files/digest-vpopmail-5.2.1-r3 :
  Changed to epatch and made the mysql patch download via mysql USE.

  06 Dec 2002; Rodney Rees <manson@gentoo.org> : changed sparc ~sparc keywords
 
  31 Oct 2002; J Robert Ray <jrray@gentoo.org> vpopmail-5.2.1-r2.ebuild :
  Remove portion of configure that forces itself to be run as root, so
  it can still be merged with portage fakeroot patches.

*vpopmail-5.2.1 (24 Jul 2002)

  07 Oct 2002; Nick Hadaway <raker@gentoo.org> vpopmail-5.2.1-r2.ebuild :
  Added vpopmail_set_homedir to pkg_postrm so comments display correct
  variable values.

  30 Jul 2002; Nick Hadaway <raker@gentoo.org>
  files/vpopmail.diff, vpopmail-5.2.1-r2.ebuild :

  Added a patch submitted by Vadim Berezniker backported from the devel
  branch of vpopmail.  Fixes some login issues.  Closes bug #5746.

  26 Feb 2002; Nicholas Jones <carpaski@gentoo.org> vpopmail-5.2.1-r2 :

  Revised -r1 submitted via consortium of Patrick Naubert and Maurizio
  Disimino to fix the library data and sandbox issues.
	
  Added homedir-via-passwd-homedir capability. Moved some code around.
  
*vpopmail-5.2.1 (24 Jul 2002)

  24 2002; Maurizio Disimino <kevin@aptbasilicata.it> ChangeLog :
  
  Vpopmail is a PITA if you turn on MySQL support. Nicholas Jones
  (carpaski@gentoo.org) wrote a patch to make our life much simpler. 
  Tnx again carpaski.
